<br>
So, back to the idea of what Skalds want.  I imagined my skald as a roving warrior, born to battle, able to hold his own in combat.  I like most of what our class has as it is, I just want to be able to withstand a single blow and be able to deal out decent damage as well.  But, hey... we are complete.  I keep thinking I will quit the game, not over this alone... but there is nothing better to play at this time, so Mythic need not worry about that.  So, more HPS, more spec points, the ability to MAYBE parry a crit attack, and more damage.<br>
<br>
Respectfully,<br>
Tuscarora, Skald 31.<br>
<br>
PS.  If you want logs, I will be happy to begin to log in the future. I made the mistake of not running a log continuously during game play. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udrgenocide.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DrGenocide</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/11/02 9:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Server and Shadowblades</span><hr size=1> Also for the record, I am a norse skald with +10 points in con from initial setup and +16 points in item bonuses.<br>
